race.description: Delta Building Automation St Leger Stakes (G3)
race.comment: MORE FELONS (6) looks ready to strike after a booming run in the G1 Metropolitan, launching from last to finish right in the mix. Finally lands a soft draw and should settle much closer this time, which makes him incredibly hard to beat out to the 2600m. His closing sectionals last start were elite and a repeat of that sees him winning. SOUL OF SPAIN (2) has been a model of consistency for the stable, just missing in the Metrop after looming large. At peak fitness now and doesn't need to find much more. Genuine danger and clearly the main threat. SAM HAWKENS (9) is the intriguing UK visitor from the powerful Haggas yard. Tough and progressive, with McDonald booked, he commands respect but faces a tough local crop. TRAVOLTA (7) is another Waller stayer building beautifully, honest as they come, while WYCLIF (8) could be the knockout late if the tempo is strong.
